<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-1077 </DOCNO><TEXT>We report our experience concerning more than 1250 chest X-rays on patientsin intensive care; these have been carried out since December 1987, usinga digital system. The method produces improvement in the radiologicaldiagnosis of patients in intensive care; this is due to avoidance ofincorrect exposures, the ability to obtain lateral films, consistentexposures and the ability to manipulate and store images electronically.(orig./GDG).</TEXT></DOC>